to calm my nerves.

10:02.046 --> 10:03.145
Here we go.

10:03.147 --> 10:04.780
You're hiding booze?

10:04.782 --> 10:06.882
It's for emergencies,
and that script is an emergency.

10:06.884 --> 10:09.818
Needing alcohol to cope
is the emergency.

10:09.820 --> 10:11.987
You're my maid, Carmen.

10:11.989 --> 10:13.055
Not my mom.

10:13.057 --> 10:15.958
So, if you don't mind...

10:17.493 --> 10:19.494
I appreciate you meeting
with me, Mrs. Parker.

10:19.496 --> 10:21.163
It's my pleasure.

10:21.165 --> 10:24.732
Mr. dresden tells me that
we have a "friend" in common.

10:24.734 --> 10:27.569
What's he calling himself
these days?

10:27.571 --> 10:28.836
Tony Bishara.

10:28.838 --> 10:31.339
He presented himself
as a bodyguard.

10:31.341 --> 10:33.308
He told me he was a chef.

10:33.310 --> 10:34.742
Tony knows how to cook?

10:34.744 --> 10:35.843
Not really.

10:35.845 --> 10:38.179
But he was attentive and caring

10:38.181 --> 10:41.315
and looked at me
with desire in his eyes,

10:41.317 --> 10:44.518
something my husband
hadn't done for years.

10:44.520 --> 10:45.853
And with that body of his,

10:45.855 --> 10:46.988
